 @Orome96  Quote from the SOMA wiki: "This revelation results in another heated argument between both Simon and Catherine; however, Catherine becomes too stressed, resulting in her overloading her circuits, effectively deactivating herself and, in turn, the Omnitool, leaving Simon stranded in the station alone."

So slight correction on my part, it's stress, more than emotions. Point still stands, the official version is the omnitool breaking due to her outburst, and the facility shutdown being due to it. That's why her voice progressively gets worse during her final sentence. That's why the screen after her crash says cortex chip corrupted.

Though, think what you will, in the end it's open to interpretation, so if you like your version better than the one other people agreed apon, don't let me stand in your way :)

 @Orome96  I agree, it makes it even more hopeless of a situation for Simon. But I guess that's exactly what they intended, so it works out in the story's favor.

As for the WAU creating more copies of him: For all we know, it might have. Or perhaps it created others the same way before shutting down. The question is, even if Simon found them, what would be the point? The ark is launched, his only way off this hell on earth is gone. All his hopes gone with it. I personally don't think Simon would have any motivation left at that point anyway. But that's just speculation on my part now ^^ 

In any case, I think the game does an excellent job of giving the player that feeling of despair Simon must feel in that moment, and ending it right there only makes it so much worse, since it leaves it to one's imagination.
